  "content": "# Dev-Loop Issue Template: Formalized Process\n\n**Date:** 2026-03-28\n**Doc:** .agents/skills/dev-loop/ISSUE-TEMPLATE.md\n\n## Decision\n\nGitHub issues intended for dev-loop execution follow a standardized template with these sections: Context, Goal, Design Reference, Prompt, Acceptance Criteria, Labels, Dependencies, Files Likely Changed.\n\n## Key Principles\n\n1. **One dev-loop run per issue.** Each issue completable in a single autonomous session (30-90 min).\n2. **Design-complete issues skip brainstorming.** If the issue links to an approved RFC section, the Prompt says \"Skip brainstorming, proceed to implementation planning.\"\n3. **Acceptance criteria are the contract.** Specific, observable, verifiable by running commands. Not vague.\n4. **Labels drive dynamic reviewers.** `security` label adds Security Engineer + Compliance. `enhancement` adds Domain Expert + DevEx.\n5. **Prompt is for the agent.** Written assuming no prior conversation context. References specific files, functions, patterns.\n\n## First Application\n\nAgent Teams adapter RFC broken into 4 issues:\n- #58: Phase 1 hooks (no deps, can start immediately)\n- #59: Phase 2 adapter extension (depends on #58)\n- #60: Phase 3 graph edges + identity correlation (depends on #59)\n- #61: Phase 4 LLM extraction + scope promotion (depends on #60)\n",
  "source_version": "mcp",
